Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the #pot{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put a #large frying pan{} on high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and fry until browned all over, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and sweetcorn. Fry, stirring occasionally, until starting to brown, ~{4-5%mins} more.

Once browned, lower the heat to medium.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%secs}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Once the spinach has wilted, add the @creme fraiche{100%g} and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

Bring to the boil, stirring, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Mix in half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and gently mix until well coated, reheating quickly if necessary.

Serve your chorizo and sweetcorn pasta in #large bowls{} with the remaining cheese sprinkled on top to finish. Enjoy!